Wash and dry produce.

Cut @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch slices.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry; place between two large pieces of #plastic wrap{}.
Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until chicken is about 1⁄2 inch thick. Season
all over with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Drizzle @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a hot large pan. Add chicken; cook until browned
and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> While chicken cooks, move on to the next step!

In the last minute of cooking, carefully spoon half the @pesto{1/2%cup} over chicken;
top with a layer of sliced mozzarella. Cover pan until cheese melts.

Thinly slice @tomato{1} into rounds.

Halve and toast @ciabatta rolls{2}.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss @arugula{4%ounce} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}
(large drizzle for 4).

Spread cut sides of ciabatta halves with remaining pesto.

Place cheesy pesto chicken on bottom ciabatta halves. Top with tomato and as much
arugula as you like. Close sandwiches.

Drizzle remaining arugula with as much @balsamic glaze{5%teaspoon} as you like;
sprinkle with @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}. Serve salad alongside sandwiches.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.